Arch Linux package manager


# Sync database

Install package:

    pacman -S package
    pacman -sync package

Update all package:

    pacman -S -u
    pacman --sync --update

Search for a package:

    pacman -S -s packagename
    pacman --sync --search packagename

Refresh the sync database:

    pacman -S -y
    pacman --sync --refresh


# Query

Print all installed packages:

    pacman -Q
    pacman --query

Info of a package:

    pacman -Q -i package
    pacman -query --info package

Packages installed as dependencies:

    pacman -Q -d
    pacman --query --deps

Orphaned dependencies:

    pacman -Q -d -t

Check health of a package (remove package to show all packages):

    pacman -Q -k packages
    pacman --query --check packages
    package: 1208 total files, 0 missing files

List all files owned by a package:

    pacman -Q -l package
    pacman --query --list package

Outdated packages:

    pacman -Q -u
    pacman --query --upgrades

# AUR packages

Warning: `yaourt` is not secure and is deprecated. It was used before.

To instal a package:

Localize the package in <https://aur.archlinux.org> and then:

    git clone https://aur.archlinux.org/PACKAGE.git
    cd PACKAGE
    makepkg -Acis

